@startuml
title UC03 — Student selects level during onboarding to create personalized roadmap — State Diagram
skinparam state {
  BackgroundColor #FEFEFE
  BorderColor #333333
  FontName Helvetica
}

[*] --> NotOnboarded
NotOnboarded --> SelectingLevel : enter app after registration
RoadmapReady --> SelectingLevel : update level in profile/onboarding

SelectingLevel --> CompletingQuestions : choose A1-C2 manually
CompletingQuestions --> Validating : submit selected level + answers

Validating --> ValidationError : missing/invalid level or required answers
ValidationError --> SelectingLevel : fix input

Validating --> LevelSaved : valid submission
LevelSaved --> LoadingLevelContent : use selected level
LoadingLevelContent --> GeneratingRoadmap : active Langeek/Admin content exists
LoadingLevelContent --> ContentFallback : no active level content
ContentFallback --> RoadmapReady : keep selected level saved
GeneratingRoadmap --> RoadmapReady : roadmap created
RoadmapReady --> [*]

note right of SelectingLevel
  User selects one of:
  A1, A2, B1, B2, C1, C2.
  No scored assessment flow.
end note

note right of LoadingLevelContent
  Filter active topics, vocabulary,
  and activities by selected level.
  Content may be Langeek-crawled
  or Admin-managed.
end note
@enduml
